<figureCitation id="B79104F60D32A400FD35FA8F3C28037C" box="[736,851,1358,1384]" captionStart-0="Figs 6–10" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="4.[189,242,1925,1951]" captionStartId-1="5.[189,232,1954,1980]" captionTargetBox-0="[248,1332,280,1880]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1398,1220,1916]" captionTargetId-0="figure-12@4.[222,1366,265,1890]" captionTargetId-1="figure-295@5.[189,1398,1220,1916]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="Figs 6–10. Oecetis apelqvisti sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (NHRS). 6. Genitalia, lateral view. 7. Genitalia, dorsal view. 8. Genitalia, ventral view. 9. Phallus, lateral view. 10. Phallus, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 11. Map with the position of the two sampling sites in Maliau Basin shown as orange dots. The position of the Maliau Basin area on Borneo is indicated with a blue rectangular in the upper-left map." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6564537" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6564540" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6564537/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6564540/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Figs 6–11</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="67B04BF80D32A400FF68FA513C41009D" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2F1518730D32A400FF68FA513E4D03BE" blockId="3.[189,310,1424,1450]" box="[189,310,1424,1450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<heading id="745DAF1F0D32A400FF68FA513E4D03BE" bold="true" box="[189,310,1424,1450]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" reason="3">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D32A400FF68FA513E4D03BE" bold="true" box="[189,310,1424,1450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F1518730D32A400FF68FA7F3C41009D" blockId="3.[188,1400,1470,1673]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
The species is distinguished from many of the Oriental and Palearctic species by the absence of modified tergites on segment VI–VIII. It resembles 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D32A400FD60FA233CC403E8" authority="Malicky, 2005" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[693,959,1505,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idas">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D32A400FD60FA233C7703E8" box="[693,780,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">O. idas</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4B3B65820D32A400FCC1FA233CC403E8" author="Malicky H." box="[788,959,1505,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="605 - 669" refId="ref2697" refString="Malicky H. 2005. Beitrage zur Kenntnis asiatischer Oecetis (Trichoptera, Leptoceridae). Linzer biologische Beitrage 27: 605 - 669." type="journal article" year="2005">
Malicky, 
<quantity id="E852B5960D32A400FC51FA203CC403E8" box="[900,959,1505,1532]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0927" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" unit="in" value="2005.0">2005</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in genitalic features, particularly the long and slightly curving superior appendages, long and strongly ventrally curving tergum X, with right branch longer than left branch, and long pair of dorsal processes. 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D32A400FC35F9E93BCE0056" authority="Johanson &amp; Malm &amp; Sjöberg, 2022" authorityName="Johanson &amp; Malm &amp; Sjöberg" authorityYear="2022" box="[992,1205,1576,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apelqvisti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D32A400FC35F9E93BCE0056" box="[992,1205,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Oecetis apelqvisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="06ED791A0D32A400FB15F9E83A660057" box="[1216,1309,1577,1603]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D32A400FE75F98D3E8F0071" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[416,500,1611,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idas">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D32A400FE75F98D3E8F0071" box="[416,500,1611,1638]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">O. idas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lateral view by the clearly bifid inferior appendages, and the apical part of phallus with a single hook-shaped sclerotized process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="67B04BF80D32A400FF68F9713BAC00ED" box="[189,1239,1712,1785]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" type="etymology">
